subSubSection.paragraph:
Terminalia
(
Fig. 6
): Cerci in posterior view, enlarged and long, twice longer than its width, almost with the same length of surstyli, apically furcated, with an acute point on each side and among them a median apical process (
Fig. 6B
). Surstyli narrow and slightly curved (
Fig. 6C
). Hypopygium (
Fig. 6D, E
) of the 

Botanophila

- 
type
, i.e. pregonite reduced and shallow, firmly connected to the central plate of hypandrium, and with 2 long setae; postgonite twice longer than the pregonite; epiphallus and distiphallus reduced; distiphallus largely membranous except for a pair of anterobasal sclerotized rods (
Fig. 6D, E
); phallapodema long and apically enlarged in dorsal (
Fig. 6E
) and lateral (
Fig. 6D
) view.

